         </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Strategy<br>
<br>
Card / Site Choices:<br>
<br>
Sam, Faithful Companion - He is cool because I can get a -1 twilight from using him to download Bill the Pony. Use him twice, once before underground, once after. Then, let him die or whatever you want.<br>
<br>
Pursuit Just Behind - I&#39;ve played this deck about 4 times just today against one of my friends. When I first showed him the deck his first question was, &quot;Why have Pursuit Just Behind?&quot; Well, Pursuit Just Behind requirs nothing. Just spot a ranger and wound. Exhausted minions go bye bye. Great against Equea and Isengard Orcs.<br>
<br>
Now... On to the real strategy.<br>
<br>
Bid low maybe even none. It doesn&#39;t matter whether you go first or not. It&#39;s good though to go second. You should let the opponent double move and use your Site 2 and 3. Then, truck to site 4. Grab the stuff needed throw it down fast. Don&#39;t discard everything... yet. Throw down They Are Coming, discard practically everything not needed at that time. Use Frodo and Aragorn to fight. Sam is a chump.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=25949"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=25949" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
